HTTP IN DETAIL:
HTTP protocol is used to request content from a web server.
what is HTTP?
HYPERTEXT TRANSFER PROTOCOL
HTTP is what's used whenever you view a website developed by TIM BERNERS-LEE & his team between 1989-1991.
HTTP is the set of rules used for communicating with web servers for the transmitting of webpage data, whether that is HTML, images, videos, etc.
what is HTTPS?
HYPERTEXT TRANSFER PROTOCOL SECURE
HTTPS is the secure version of HTTP.
HTTPS data is encrypted so it not only stops people from seeing the data you are receiving & sending,
but it also gives you assurances that you're talking to the correct web server & not something impersonating it.
